Zi Ting (Louisa) You

School

Hello World! I’m a PhD student in Psychology at the University of Toronto, studying intergroup relations, minority coalitions, and political psychology. For more information about my work, please check out my CV. Or, visit the SPRQLab website (it is much nicer, I promise). The eminent Dr. Elizabeth Page-Gould is my doctoral advisor.

If you’re interested in the meta-analysis on the effects of intergroup contact on affective polarization, more information is here. This analysis will be part of a mega-paper coming soon.

It’s Louisa for friends and You, Z. for citations, thank you!

Non-School

I recently finished a contract position as a Research Assistant with the Behavioural Science Office at the Public Health Office of Canada. My work was on strategic foresight and science communication.

I’m a frequenter of various bakeries downtown and it is my dream to become a regular extra at one of these places. Please send me your best chocolate chip cookie to be considered.
